The paper focuses on improving the performance of 3D object detection using LiDAR point clouds, which is a common task in computer vision (cs.CV) and robotics (cs.RO). The proposed approach involves using a sequence of small networks and a spatial transformation mechanism, which are techniques commonly used in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions evaluating the proposed approach using KITTI dataset, which is a common benchmark dataset in natural language processing (cs.CL).
